story.title: Unseen and Unheard - Episode 5
story.storyDescription: Why is Heather’s boyfriend talking to her like she isn’t there?
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Charlie Poe is a former Virginia police officer who enjoys writing mysteries and horror. Follow him to read more stories like Unseen and Unheard.

story.prePaywallNotification: OMG! Professor Thomas wants to kill Heather?! 😱 Tap back into Hooked to see if she survives.
story.postPaywallNotification: OMG—Heather can feel Kira’s hand… does this mean she’ll be able to go back into the real world? Tap back into Hooked to find out.

messages.text: HEATHER! RUN!
You can try to run…
But I’m still going to kill you.
Heather screams blindly, trying to cast her voice toward her friends.
Help me!
Heather! Run towards my voice!
Heather lunges, but Professor Thomas heard Jax’s directive too.
He grabs Heather’s arm.
Jax! Help — he’s got me!
I do. You can’t escape now…
Heather feels cold metal against her temple as she realizes Professor Thomas is holding a gun to her head.
Jax! He’s got a gun…
No! I won’t let him hurt you.
YOU CAN’T STOP ME!
Jax, I’m not going to make it.
Heather run!
Use all your strength  — try to break free and get out of there!
I’m not strong enough.
Jax, I just want to say…I love you.
I love you, Heather. I wish I could hold you right now.
Kira? I love you too. You’re my best friend.
You’re my best friend too, Heather.
I’m reaching for your hand…just like before, at the Pizzeria.
Can you squeeze it, so I can at least pretend to feel it?
Wait. I do feel it.
Me too! I’m pulling.
What? What is going on?
Heather disappears from the alternate universe.
Where did you go!?
Sorry, Professor. She’s back with us now.
You crossed the border? Again?
But how??
Oh my God, what just happened?
I’m back!!
Heather throws her arms around Kira and then Jax.
But before she can kiss him, Professor Thomas’s voice thunders in.
They spring apart.
Professor Thomas must be very close.
This isn’t possible!
No matter. I’ll come back through—
A gun will work in any dimension.
Just try and kill us, dirtbag. Everyone, to the car, NOW.
WHAT?! The border…
It closed? But how did this happen??
Kira lets out the breath she was holding while Jax cheers.
Oh my God, we are SO lucky…
Enjoy life on the other side, Professor!
Wait, it shouldn’t just close like this!
Damn it, I will find a way through!
I will destroy you! I will destroy you all!
Have fun with that, weirdo.
I WILL find a way out of this dimension—
And when I do, I’ll kill all of you!
Enjoy your stay, creep…
The next morning, Heather gets a text from Kira.
Hey — how are you feeling?
You blacked out almost immediately in the car.
Yeah. I mean, fielding questions from the police and my parents hasn’t been easy.
It’s been hard explaining how I’m still alive.
I get that. But I wasn’t talking about them—
I was asking about YOU, Heather.
How do YOU feel?
I guess I’m still a little weird and tingly from when you pulled me across that border.
How did we do that?
Heather, I can’t explain anything that happened over the last few days…
But you know what?
I’m fine with that.
I’m fine never thinking about, talking about, or otherwise reliving it ever again.
Amen to that.
You’re back, and that is all I care about.
Yeah. Me too.
I have a hunch, though…
You do?
Yeah. It’s going to sound a little cheesy but…
What if you’re the reason I came back?
What if it was our friendship that helped me break through?
Aww, are you saying our powers of love defeated evil?
Haha, I know it sounds stupid, but…yes.
I’m so lucky we’re friends, Kira. And I love you.
I am too. LYLAS lol 👯‍
So, is Jax over there with you?
Yes. He’s napping on the couch.
My parents don’t want to deprive him of time with me, but they also won’t let him upstairs.
They said something about our “raging teenage hormones.”
I mean, you already died and came back?
Well technically, I didn’t die. And even though my mom’s over the moon that I’m alive…
She’s still petrified of teen pregnancy.
She said if I make her a grandmother before she’s 50 she’ll ship me off to a convent.
A convent? Wow, THAT might actually be worse than death.
Doubtful.
So…what do we do now?
We try to get on with our lives, I guess.
Yeah…
On that note, want to come over and watch a movie? We can give Jax a makeover while he’s asleep.
Haha, YESSS. I’ll grab my kit and be there in 20.
LOL see you soon.
What flavor ice cream would you like?
Is this Heather?
Who is this?
A friend.
I thought you might like to know that I have a message for you.
Kira? I just got a really creepy text message.
But Kira doesn’t respond.
Would you like to hear the message?
Who are you?
What do you want?
The message is…
THIS IS KIRA AND YOU JUST GOT PLAYED!
LMAO
DUDE. Not cool!
Oh, please. You love me and you’re laughing.
Maybe a little bit. And it does feel good. It’s been a crazy few days.
But I’m still worried…
Like, what if *he* figures a way out…
Then we’ll beat him again.
But for now, let’s try to get back to something normal.
That means inside jokes and an ungodly amount of pizza and tacos…
And enough makeup on Jax’s dumb sleeping face to make someone who works at Sephora blush.
LOL ok.
See you in a bit — I’m going to put my phone away. After all this, texting and driving doesn’t seem like a great idea.
Good call.
And Heather?
Yeah?
I’m glad you’re ok.
Me too.
And now, everything can start getting back to normal.
